Two issues:

```js
methods: {
   integrationsTableItems () {
      return {
         { model: this.variable },
      }
   }
}
```

Should be:

```js
methods: {
   integrationsTableItems () {
      // b-table expects an array of items, not an object
      return [
         { model: this.variable },
      ]
   }
}
```

The second issue is that you are passing the _value_ of `this.variable` into your items, not the reactive getter/setter bound to your component data. Updating the item&#39;s `model` field will only update it&#39;s value in the item object, and not the value in data.

If there is only one variable in data, then do the following:

```html
&lt;b-table class=&quot;settings-integrationsTable&quot; outlined :items=&quot;integrationsTableItems()&quot; :fields=&quot;print_integrations_fields&quot;&gt;
   &lt;template v-slot:cell(switch)=&quot;data&quot;&gt;
      &lt;!-- &quot;model&quot; will point to this.model (your data) --&gt;
      &lt;b-form-checkbox type=&quot;checkbox&quot; v-model=&quot;model&quot;&gt;
      &lt;/b-form-checkbox&gt;
   &lt;/template&gt;
&lt;/b-table&gt;
```

### Update (2019-10-10):

To place a getter/setter in your items data (for the item property `model`):

```js
   integrationsTableItems () {
      return [
         {
           model: {
             get() =&gt; {
               return this.variable
             },
             set(val) =&gt; {
               this.variabel = val
             }
           }
         },
      ]
   }
```

